# MixAuto Android Car Launcher

Custom HOME launcher for Eonon head units. Jetpack Compose + Material 3, sensor orientation (portrait + landscape), automotive-grade dark UI.

## Stack

- Package: `com.kyuusanq3.mixauto`
- Compose BOM `2024.06.00`, Kotlin `1.9.24`, Compose Compiler `1.5.14`
- Entry: `MainActivity` → `MixAutoTheme` → `DashboardScreen`
- See `AGENTS.md` at repo root for full layout and build instructions

## UI rules

- Use `MixAutoTheme`; never light mode — head unit is always dark
- Colors: `OledBlack`, `DeepCharcoal`, `DarkSurface`, `ElectricCyan` from `ui/theme/Color.kt`
- Sizes: `CarDimensions` object — min tap target 64dp, primary 84dp
- Text: prefer `CarHeadlineText`, `CarBodyText`, `CarLabelText` from `ui/theme/Type.kt` (ellipsis + maxLines enforced)
- Import theme text composables explicitly when used in dashboard files

## Layout structure

- `DashboardScreen.kt`: portrait Column (map → media → horizontal dock) or landscape Row/Column; map via `CarMapViewContainer` | media + shortcuts; `mapMediaRatio` slider in settings (default 0.6)
- Map: `CarMapEngine` interface in `domain/map/`; swap `MapLibreEngineImpl()` in `MainActivity` only
- `CarMapViewContainer.kt`: `AndroidView` + lifecycle forwarding + HUD + search overlay trigger
- `ShortcutDock.kt`: three-zone dock — driver cluster (App Drawer + **Voice Search mic**) | centered **pinned apps (up to 5)** | **music side control** (`DockMusicSideControl`: horizontal track text / vertical `DockMiniVisualizer` when collapsed, cyan MusicNote when media pane open); **Launcher settings** gear in `AppDrawerOverlay` header; Map Data on map toolbar only; `ActivePanel.APP_DRAWER` opens `AppDrawerOverlay` over map+media only (shortcut bar stays visible)

## Map engine architecture

```
MainActivity (mapEngine = MapLibreEngineImpl())
  └── DashboardScreen(mapEngine)
        └── CarMapViewContainer(engine)
              ├── AndroidView → MapLibreEngineImpl.createMapView()
              ├── HUD from engine.uiState.collectAsState()
              └── NavigationSearchOverlay → searchDestination() / navigateToCoordinates()
```

- Style: inline OSM raster JSON (`tile.openstreetmap.org`) — not `demotiles.maplibre.org` (no PH coverage)
- Routing: `routing.openstreetmap.de/routed-car` OSRM API (not `router.project-osrm.org` — returns 403); `User-Agent: MixAutoCarLauncher/1.0` required; route line via GeoJsonSource + LineLayer `#00CBD6`
- Search: Nominatim with `User-Agent: MixAutoCarLauncher/1.0`
- Location: `MapLibreFusedLocationEngineImpl` (AOSP, no Google Services dep); runtime `ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION` + `ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION` both requested
- No `play-services-location` dependency — app must work on Eonon/AOSP devices without Google Play Services

## Shortcut packages (Eonon / AOSP)

- Settings: `com.android.settings`
- Radio: try `com.android.fmradio`, `com.caf.fmradio`, `com.eonon.radio`
- Bluetooth: settings package or `Settings.ACTION_BLUETOOTH_SETTINGS` fallback

## Manifest

- HOME + DEFAULT + LAUNCHER intent-filters on `MainActivity`
- `launchMode="singleTask"`, `screenOrientation="sensor"`

## Build (Windows CLI)

Set `JAVA_HOME` to Android Studio `jbr` before `.\gradlew.bat assembleDebug`.

## Lessons learned

- Missing import for `CarLabelText` in `DashboardScreen.kt` caused compile failure — always import all `Car*Text` composables used in a file
- Kotlin and Compose Compiler versions must stay paired in `gradle/libs.versions.toml`
- Removed `activity_main.xml`; dashboard is 100% Compose — do not recreate XML main layout
- Gradle in Cursor terminal may fail without `JAVA_HOME`; Android Studio build works with embedded JDK
- MapView lifecycle race: `DisposableEffect` calls `onStart`/`onResume` before `AndroidView` factory runs — call `view.onStart()`/`view.onResume()` in `createMapView()` after `onCreate(null)`
- MapLibre 11.x removed `LocationEngineProvider` — use `LocationEngineProxy(AndroidLocationEngineImpl(ctx))` for emulator compatibility
- `demotiles.maplibre.org` has limited regional coverage; use OSM raster tiles for Philippines/global
- Map loads before location permission dialog — `MainActivity` must call `retryLocationActivation()` when permission already granted, not only after dialog
- Emulator mock GPS: `getLastKnownLocation` often null until `requestLocationUpdates(GPS_PROVIDER, …)` fires; refresh on `onResume` after Extended Controls changes
- `CarMapViewContainer` needs `lifecycle-runtime-compose` for `LocalLifecycleOwner`
- After OSRM route draw, `showRouteThenDive()` shows a 2 s `LatLngBounds` overview then dives to `CameraMode.TRACKING_GPS` (zoom 17.5, tilt 55°) — do not set `TRACKING` immediately after route draw or it snaps back before the dive
- `ShortcutDock` item keys must stay stable (`voice_search`, `app_drawer`, `dock_music_control`, `dock_pinned_$packageName`); wrap horizontal/vertical branches in `key(isHorizontal, isLeftHandDrive)` — toggling layout or LHD changes icon order and can crash with duplicate keys
- Cached `MapView` in `MapLibreEngineImpl.createMapView()`: detach from parent via `(parent as? ViewGroup)?.removeView()` before returning to a new `AndroidView`
- Do not call `engine.onDestroy()` in `CarMapViewContainer` composable `onDispose` — only forward `ON_DESTROY` from activity lifecycle; layout changes remove/re-add the composable but must keep the map engine alive
- Emulator GPS (`adb emu geo fix`, Extended Controls) delivers 0 location reports on some AVDs — this is an AVD-level failure, not an app bug; test location on a physical device
- `MapLibreEngineImpl` registers GPS location listener ONCE via `listenersRegistered` flag — do not tear down and re-register on every `onResume`; rapid re-registration causes AppOps `op=GPS: Operation not started` errors and no fixes are delivered
- `forceLocationUpdate(location)` on `locationComponent` is required to push fixes into MapLibre's blue dot; store fix in `pendingLocationFix` if component not yet activated, flush in `activateLocationTracking()`
- `navigateToCoordinates()` falls back to map camera center (`resolveMapViewOrigin()`) when GPS is null and camera zoom ≥ 10 — allows routing on emulator without GPS fix
- Do NOT add `play-services-location` or any `com.google.android.gms` dependency — app targets AOSP head units with no Google Services
- `router.project-osrm.org` returns 403 for third-party apps — use `routing.openstreetmap.de/routed-car` in `fetchOsrmRoute()`; set `User-Agent: MixAutoCarLauncher/1.0` on OSRM requests (same as Nominatim)
- Turn-by-turn navigation: `fullRouteSteps` / `currentStepIndex` in `MapLibreEngineImpl`; `evaluateStepAdvancement()` runs on GPS fixes when `isNavigating` — do not overwrite `streetName` with "Current location" during navigation
- Step advance threshold 25 m; arrival at 15 m from destination or when step index exhausts; `navigationArrivalTriggered` prevents duplicate arrival coroutines
- `startFreeDrive()` removes route layer/source, resets `MapUiState`, snaps once via `snapCameraToGpsIfNeeded()` — do not re-snap on every GPS fix (causes camera twitching)
- Free drive camera: `FREE_DRIVE_ZOOM` 17.5 / `FREE_DRIVE_TILT` 50° / `CameraMode.TRACKING_GPS`; full nav uses zoom 18.5 / tilt 63°
- One-time snap: `hasSnappedCameraToGps` gates `snapCameraToGpsIfNeeded()`; use `moveCamera` then `TRACKING_GPS` — do not loop animated `setCameraMode` or stale-target checks on GPS updates
- Style-load callback calls `startFreeDrive()` after `activateLocationTracking()`; `retryLocationActivation()` must NOT call `startFreeDrive()` again (duplicate snap/twitch)
- Enabling `CameraMode.TRACKING` at wide fallback zoom (6) locks the visual view zoomed out even when `cameraPosition.zoom` reports 14–16 — snap after location component is active
- End navigation button in `CarMapViewContainer` (Close icon, red tint) calls `engine.startFreeDrive()` when `isNavigating`
- 3D nav camera: `showRouteThenDive()` sets `CameraMode.NONE` + `cancelTransitions()`, animates bounds in `ROUTE_OVERVIEW_ANIMATION_MS` (2 s), holds full-route view for `ROUTE_OVERVIEW_HOLD_MS` (10 s) with `routeOverviewProgress` timer bar in `CarMapViewContainer`; then `enterNavigationCamera()` — guard with `_uiState.value.isNavigating`; cancel `routeOverviewJob` in `startFreeDrive()`
- Nav dive camera: `enterNavigationCamera()` must NOT call `zoomWhileTracking`/`tiltWhileTracking` right after `TRACKING_GPS` — MapLibre ignores them while camera mode is transitioning; use `CameraMode.NONE` → `map.animateCamera(zoom 18.5 / tilt 63°)` → set `TRACKING_GPS` in `CancelableCallback.onFinish` (same snap pattern as free drive)
- Use `RenderMode.GPS` (not `COMPASS`) for heading-up driving view; set on `activateLocationTracking()` and before nav/free-drive camera modes
- Manual pan/zoom sets `isCameraDetached` via `MapLibreMap.OnCameraMoveStartedListener.REASON_API_GESTURE`; recenter button in `CarMapViewContainer` `MapToolbarOverlay` shows when `isCameraDetached` (**including during navigation** — `GpsFixed` below red End nav); CropFree top-down button remains **free-drive only** (`!isNavigating`); tap calls `engine.recenterCamera()` → `enterNavigationCamera()` when navigating
- `MainActivity` uses `WindowCompat.setDecorFitsSystemWindows(window, false)` + `WindowInsetsControllerCompat.show(systemBars())` — root `DashboardScreen` must apply `systemBarsPadding()` so content sits below status/nav bars; head units with zero insets get no extra padding
- Do **not** set `android:windowFullscreen` in `themes.xml` — it hides the system status/notification bar on Eonon head units; keep `windowContentOverlay` @null only
- Portrait: map `weight(mapMediaRatio)`, media `weight(1 - ratio)`, horizontal `ShortcutDock` at bottom with wrap-content height
- Landscape horizontal shortcuts: map/media split by `mapMediaRatio`; vertical shortcuts: narrow icon-only dock (`wrapContentWidth()`), map/media share remaining Row width by ratio
- Horizontal dock compact sizes: `DockHorizontalTapTarget` 48dp, `DockHorizontalIconSize` 40dp — do not reuse `MinTapTarget`/`AppIconSize` for horizontal bar
- `LauncherViewModel.updateMapMediaRatio()` not `setMapMediaRatio()` — JVM signature clash with `mapMediaRatio` property setter
- Media controls in `MediaPlayerPane.kt`: each button in `Row` needs `Modifier.weight(1f)` + `requiredSize(MinTapTarget)` or last button shrinks when pane is narrow
- Now playing: `MediaSessionRepository` + `MixAutoNotificationListenerService`; user must enable Notification access — `MediaSessionManager.getActiveSessions()` requires enabled listener component
- Shared overlay dismiss: `OverlayCloseButton` in `ui/components/` — use for full-screen dialogs (settings, search), not text Close buttons
- `MainActivity.onResume()` calls `MediaSessionRepository.refreshSessions()` after returning from notification-access settings or media apps
- Offline Overture POI build/publish tools live in sibling repo **`mix-auto-overture-maps/tools/`** — not `mix-auto/tools/`; `mix-auto/tools/README.md` is a pointer only
- App catalog: `MapDataViewModel` fetches `countries.json` from `kyuusanq3/mix-auto-overture-maps/releases/latest/download/`; per-country URL is `{RELEASE_BASE}/{asset}` from manifest — no app update needed when publishing new release tags marked Latest
- GitHub release must **attach** `countries.json` + `{iso}_places.db.gz` as release assets; a release with zero assets returns 404 on `/latest/download/` even if the tag exists
- Philippines pack sizes: ~137 MB compressed (`ph_places.db.gz`), ~263 MB installed SQLite; manifest `size_compressed_mb` / `size_db_mb` drives UI labels
- `LocalPlacesRepository.downloadDatabaseFromUrl()` decompresses `.gz`; manual `importDatabaseFromUri()` does NOT — sideload uncompressed `.db` only
- `MapDataOverlay` header copy still says "~50 MB compressed" — per-row sizes from catalog are correct (~137 MB for PH)
- Destination search distance: default **500 km** cap via `MAX_SEARCH_RADIUS_M` in `MapLibreEngineImpl`; filter runs after `mergeAndDeduplicate()` when `limitDistance` is true — local SQLite bbox (±0.5°) unchanged
- Launcher Settings toggle **"Nearby results only (within 500 km)"** (`LauncherPreferences.limitSearchDistance`, default ON) flows DashboardScreen → CarMapViewContainer → NavigationSearchOverlay → `searchDestination(limitDistance)`; include `limitSearchDistance` in search `LaunchedEffect` keys so toggling re-queries
- Photon returns global results (lat/lon is bias only); public OSRM demo server cannot reliably route intercontinental or 5000+ km trips — distance limit protects search UX, not routing capability
- POI map pins: camera-idle listener (zoom ≥ 13, 1.5 s debounce) loads local Overture bbox first then merges Photon; use `mergePoiPins()` not `mergeAndDeduplicate()` for pin layer — latter re-sorts by distance and evicts categorized local pins
- `PoiIconFactory.kt` generates category teardrop bitmaps (F/G/H/A/$/S/R/•); SymbolLayer uses data-driven `iconImage` from normalized Overture/Photon category
- Vector tiles: `LauncherPreferences.useVectorTiles` (default **true** on first launch) → `CarMapEngine.setMapStyle()`; raster OSM JSON vs OpenFreeMap Liberty `https://tiles.openfreemap.org/styles/liberty`
- App display name **Mix Auto** (`strings.xml`); theme style `Theme.MixAuto` (renamed from `Theme.MyApplication`)
- Launcher icon: `ic_launcher_background.xml` solid `#000000`, `ic_launcher_foreground.xml` cyan pin `#00E5FF` with white center dot
- **Navigation App Mode** default: `MainActivity` intent-filter is LAUNCHER only; `LauncherModeAlias` (HOME+DEFAULT) `android:enabled="false"` in manifest — enable via Settings **Launcher Mode** + `MainActivity.applyLauncherMode()` / `PackageManager.setComponentEnabledSetting(..., DONT_KILL_APP)`
- `LauncherPreferences.isLauncherMode` default false; toggled in `LauncherViewModel.toggleLauncherMode()`; restored in `onCreate()` before UI
- Current release: `versionCode = 6`, `versionName = "0.0.6"`; signed release APK at `mix-auto.apk` (project root, gitignored); upload manually to GitHub release
- Off-route reroute: `routeGeometryPoints` + `checkOffRoute()` in `evaluateStepAdvancement()` — 75 m threshold, **3** consecutive off-route fixes (`REROUTE_CONFIRM_COUNT = 3`), **20 s** cooldown, **8 s** post-maneuver grace (`offRouteGraceUntilMs`); reroute TTS deduped to once per **30 s** in `NavigationVoiceController`; `startNavigation(..., isReroute=true)` skips `showRouteThenDive()` and calls `enterNavigationCamera()` directly
- Route line vanishing on raster style: `ensureRouteLayers()` adds traveled/remaining layers above anchor (`osm`/traffic) — do not use plain `addLayer()` or line renders under tiles
- Nav puck under route/traffic: `resolvePuckLayerAnchorId()` picks `ROUTE_REMAINING_LAYER_ID` when navigating else `mix-traffic-layer` (`TRAFFIC_LAYER_ID`); `buildLocationComponentOptions()` + `ensurePuckAboveOverlays()` apply `layerAbove(anchor)` after route draw, traffic toggle, and puck scale changes — free-drive traffic must anchor puck or green lines render over the puck
- Waze-style puck: `applyDrivingViewportPadding()` — fraction-based pixel padding (`VIEWPORT_PADDING_LEFT_FRACTION=0.3`, `VIEWPORT_PADDING_TOP_FRACTION=0.4` of map view px dimensions) positions puck at ~65% from left and ~70% from top; uses `map.width`/`map.height` so it scales correctly across all screen sizes and densities; called from `activateLocationTracking()` and `applyFreeDriveToMap()`
- Media auto-play on boot: `MediaSessionRepository.maybeAutoPlay()` once per process (`hasAutoPlayed`) when session has metadata but is not `STATE_PLAYING`; call from `attachController()` **and** retry in `onMetadataChanged()` (late metadata on head unit boot) and same-token re-attach branch; requires notification access enabled; **`ensureDefaultPlayerIfNeeded()`** in `MainActivity.refreshMediaSessionsAndBootAudio()` wakes `LauncherPreferences.defaultAudioPackage` once per process via `BackgroundAudioLauncher.wakeWithForegroundFallback()` (MediaBrowser bind + play, not `launchAppByPackage`; fallback launch+refocus Mix Auto), then retries `refreshSessions()` at 2s/5s/10s; user taps still use `launchAppByPackage()`; register `OnActiveSessionsChangedListener` on first successful refresh
- Default audio source: `LauncherPreferences.defaultAudioPackage` (key `default_audio_package`, empty = unset) → `LauncherViewModel.updateDefaultAudioPackage()`; clear on init if `canLaunchApp()` fails; no default + no session → inline `AudioPlayerListContent` in `MediaPlayerPane` ("Choose the default audio source", tap sets default + launches); default set + idle → normal player + boot launch fallback; active session always wins in `selectController()`
- Audio player picker: shared `AudioPlayerListContent` in `AudioPlayerPickerOverlay.kt` — overlay tap launches app only; long-press → confirm dialog → set default; row suffix `(Default)`; overlay bottom hint **Long press to set as default** (`showLongPressHint` false in setup mode)
- Shortcut icon size: `DockShortcutIconSize` enum (`SMALL`/`MEDIUM`/`LARGE`) in `ShortcutDock.kt`; persisted via `LauncherPreferences.dockShortcutIconSize` (key `shortcut_icon_size`, ordinal 0/1/2, default **LARGE** on first launch); legacy `large_shortcut_icons` boolean migrates on read (false→SMALL, true→LARGE); Settings **Shortcut Icon Size** discrete slider (`valueRange` 0..2, `steps = 1`); scales `DockHorizontalTapTarget`/`DockHorizontalIconSize` by 1×/1.5×/2× — do not use `AppIconSize` for dock items
- Synthetic bearing in `MapLibreEngineImpl.enrichLocationWithBearing()`: when `hasBearing()` is false (emulator/mock GPS), compute heading from previous fix via `bearingTo()` if movement > 10 m — prevents north-up camera when moving without compass bearing
- Bearing freeze when stopped: `enrichLocationWithBearing()` treats stopped as speed < `STOPPED_SPEED_MPS` (1.4 m/s) **or** movement < `STOPPED_MOVE_M` (8 m) between fixes; `resolveFrozenBearing()` locks to `lastStableBearing` or current map camera bearing — **must** feed LocationComponent via `BearingEnrichedLocationEngine` wrapper (`createLocationEngine()`); enriching only in `applyAndroidLocation()` does not affect puck/camera because raw engine still drives MapLibre; app speed/HUD listens on `rawLocationEngine`, enriched engine only for LocationComponent activation
- Puck smoothing (2026-06): `SmoothingLocationEngine` speed-adaptive blend (500/700/900 ms) + light extrapolation up to 1.2 s / 30 m between GPS fixes feeds LocationComponent — no per-tick `forceLocationUpdate()`; `setMaxAnimationFps(MAX)` on tracking engage; bearing EMA (`BEARING_EMA_ALPHA`); `resetSmoothingMotion()` on camera detach, top-down, route overview, style reload
- Puck flicker fix (2026-07): single GPS subscription — `BearingEnrichedLocationEngine.onRawFix` tees HUD/nav to `onLocationFixForAppLogic()`; do NOT add second `requestLocationUpdates` on `rawLocationEngine`; while `shouldSmoothPuckMotion()` skip `forceLocationUpdateForImmediateRender` (slider path uses `allowDuringSmoothing=true` + `currentDisplayLocation()`); bucketed lookahead padding (`LOOKAHEAD_ENTER/EXIT`, 8 dp quantize); `handleMapLayoutChange` only reapplies padding when key changes; `activateFreeDriveTrackingMode` mode-change only; road-snap hysteresis (`SNAP_TO_ROUTE_RELEASE_M` 45 m); suppress bearing-only `shouldEmitPuckFix` when stopped
- **Driving tile prefetch:** `configureDrivingTilePrefetch()` after style load — `prefetchZoomDelta=3`, `setMaximumAmbientCacheSize(256MB)`; `DrivingTilePrefetcher` warms ambient cache via `putResourceWithUrl(url, bytes, modified, expires, etag, mustRevalidate)` on IO — MapLibre **11.5.1** has no callback overload; bearing-biased extra top padding in `computeDrivingViewportPadding()` when speed > 2 m/s
- **Offline detail upgrade banner:** `LauncherPreferences.offlineDetailUpgradeBannerDismissed` — Map Data shows dismissible banner when `anyRegionNeedsDetailUpgrade()`; user must tap **Update** per region (z14 packs not auto-deleted on app update)
- Route line styling: traveled/remaining split — grey `#6B7280` (`ROUTE_TRAVELED_*` layers) for passed segment, cyan `#00CBD6` (`ROUTE_REMAINING_*`) ahead; `updateRouteProgress()` on GPS fix with monotonic advance; puck above route/traffic via `resolvePuckLayerAnchorId()` + `ensurePuckAboveOverlays()` after `drawRoute()`
- Route line width: `ROUTE_WIDTH` 14f with casing 18f `#CC000000` below each line half; remove all four route layers + two sources in `applyFreeDriveToMap()` via `removeRouteLayers()`
- Android Studio AVD x86_64 GPS (all API levels, Google Play and AOSP images): `adb emu geo fix` returns `OK` but `Number of location reports: 0` — GNSS HAL is broken; workaround is `avd-gps.ps1` at repo root which uses `cmd location providers add-test-provider gps` after `adb root`
- Android 12+ (API 31) `cmd location providers` mock GPS: `LocationManagerService.addTestProvider` calls `noteOp(OP_MOCK_LOCATION, callingUid, "android")` — default mode is `MODE_ERRORED`; `appops set shell android:mock_location allow` does NOT work (wrong package/uid binding); must grant by uid number: `cmd appops set 0 MOCK_LOCATION allow` and `cmd appops set 2000 MOCK_LOCATION allow` (as root) before calling `cmd location providers`
- `avd-gps.ps1`: run once per emulator boot; `.\avd-gps.ps1` for single fix at Gov Center, `.\avd-gps.ps1 -Drive` for 39 road-snapped fixes Gov Center → SM City Bacolod via OSRM, `.\avd-gps.ps1 LAT LNG` for custom fix
- PowerShell URL construction with doubles: always use `InvariantCulture` formatting and concatenate query string separately — PowerShell 7 null-conditional `?.` parses `$varS?query` as null-conditional in double-quoted strings, silently dropping the variable value
- Release signing: keystore at `app/mixauto-release.jks` (alias `mixauto`, RSA 2048, 10 000-day validity); `signingConfigs { create("release") }` in `app/build.gradle.kts`; credentials stored in plaintext (personal sideload only — move to `keystore.properties` before Play Store)
- Release APK workflow: `.\gradlew.bat assembleRelease` → copy to `mix-auto.apk` at repo root; use `/local-apk` (build + release notes) or `/local-apk publish` (also commit, push `dev`, GitHub release + APK upload); publish script at `~/.cursor/skills/local-apk/scripts/publish-release.ps1` — needs `gh auth login` or `$env:GITHUB_TOKEN` (repo scope); install gh on Windows: `winget install --id GitHub.cli -e`, open new terminal for PATH
- `/local-apk` skill commit message is derived from **local uncommitted changes on dev** (`git diff --stat` + `git diff --stat --cached` + `git log --oneline -10`) — NOT from `main..dev` diff; the `main..dev` range covers the full branch history and produces an overly broad commit message
- `mix-auto.apk` and `app/mixauto-release.jks` should be in `.gitignore`
- TomTom traffic overlay: `LauncherPreferences.showTraffic` + `tomTomApiKey`; `MapLibreEngineImpl.applyTrafficOverlay()` adds `RasterSource` via `TileSet("2.1.0", url)` (not direct URL constructor — `{z}/{x}/{y}` placeholder bug); layer IDs `mix-traffic-source` / `mix-traffic-layer`; Orbis v2 URL `https://api.tomtom.com/maps/orbis/traffic/flow/raster/tile/{z}/{x}/{y}?apiVersion=2&key={KEY}&style=light&tileSize=256` — valid styles **`light`** and **`dark`** only
- TomTom key check: `TomTomTrafficClient.verifyApiKey()` + inline **`NetworkCheck` trailing icon** on TomTom key `OutlinedTextField` (`TomTomApiKeySection` in `MapDataOverlay.kt`); spinner in trailing slot while checking — no full-width Test button; `LauncherViewModel.updateTomTomApiKey()` not `setTomTomApiKey()` (JVM signature clash with property setter)
- TomTom + traffic UI: **Traffic Overlay** toggle grouped under TomTom API key in `TomTomApiKeySection` — not a separate row in `MapSettingsPanelContent`; `MapDataSectionContent` takes `showTraffic` + `onToggleTraffic` (optional, null hides toggle in unused `MapDataOverlay` dialog path)
- Google Places POI caching prohibited by Google Maps Platform ToS even when device has Play Services; TomTom Places or Overture offline DB are cache-friendly alternatives
- Recent destinations: `LauncherPreferences.recentDestinations` JSON (max 10, 50 m dedup); `LauncherViewModel.addRecentDestination()`; wired MainActivity → DashboardScreen → CarMapViewContainer → NavigationSearchOverlay via `onDestinationSelected`
- Saved places: `LauncherPreferences.savedPlaces` JSON (max 50, 50 m dedup); `LauncherViewModel.toggleSavedPlace()` / `isPlaceSaved()`; wired MainActivity → DashboardScreen → CarMapViewContainer → NavigationSearchOverlay via `onToggleSavedPlace`
- Map tap anywhere: `MapLibreEngineImpl.addOnMapClickListener` — POI pin hit uses feature props; empty tap finds nearest `poiCache` entry within `MAP_TAP_NEAREST_POI_MAX_M` (500 m) or creates `SearchResultPlace("Dropped Pin", isDroppedPin=true)` with `formatLatLng` subtitle
- POI details drawer: `PoiDetailDrawer.kt` rendered at **DashboardScreen** root `Box` (full screen, covers media pane) — not inside `CarMapViewContainer`; Navigate calls `onDestinationSelected` + `navigateToCoordinates`; star calls `onToggleSavedPlace`
- Starred map pins: `CarMapEngine.setSavedPlaces()` → `savedPlacesKeys` (lat/lng rounded 5 dp) → GeoJSON `starred` property → `poiCategoryIconExpression()` uses `Expression.switchCase` for gold `poi_icon_starred_*` icons from `PoiIconFactory`
- Empty search overlay: **Recent + Nearby** suggestions when `query.length < 2`; header star toggle (`savedFilterActive`) shows saved-only list and local text filter when typed; each `SearchResultRow` has star `IconButton`; typed normal-mode results also show star button
- Destination search saved filter: `savedFilterActive` in `NavigationSearchOverlay.kt` — star in `PanelHeaderRow.trailingContent` (`PanelCompactHeaderTapTarget` sizing); **+** icon beside star opens `ActivePanel.ADD_PLACE` (`AddPlaceFromLinkContent`); when ON, `filterSavedPlaces()` filters `displayedSaved` locally (name/subTitle, case-insensitive) — do NOT call `searchDestination` or `getNearbyPois`; progress bar gated with `!savedFilterActive`; placeholder `"Search saved places"`; toggle is ephemeral `remember` (resets when panel remounts)
- Map/media split: draggable 3-dot `MapMediaDividerHandle` on pane seam in `DashboardScreen.kt` (not Settings slider); ratio 0.3–0.8 persisted via `LauncherPreferences.mapMediaRatio` / `LauncherViewModel.updateMapMediaRatio()`
- Overlay split lock: when `activePanel == ActivePanel.SEARCH`, `ActivePanel.ADD_PLACE`, or `ActivePanel.POI_DETAIL`, use `effectiveMapMediaRatio = OVERLAY_MAP_MEDIA_RATIO` (**0.4f** — 40% map / 60% secondary) for layout weights and hide divider via `showMapMediaDivider`; do NOT call `updateMapMediaRatio(0.4f)` — persisted ratio unchanged so dismiss restores user's prior split; Settings / Map Data / Media unaffected
- Map/media divider drag: never put `mapMediaRatio` in `pointerInput` keys — each ratio update restarts the detector and breaks continuous drag; use `rememberUpdatedState` + `onDragStart` + accumulated `totalDragPx`
- Map/media divider touch target: do not use `MinTapTarget` as layout width/height in Row/Column — use `seamTouchTarget` layout modifier (0 dp seam, 64 dp hit area placed centered overlapping panes); RHD horizontal shortcuts need `invertDrag = true`
- Puck position sliders: flow through `setViewportPadding()` → `applyPuckPaddingUpdate()` — while `TRACKING_GPS`, update `paddingWhileTracking` only (skip `applyDrivingViewportPadding` / `moveCamera(paddingTo)`); `handleMapLayoutChange` compares padding key before reapply (no unconditional cache clear); slider force uses `allowDuringSmoothing=true`; if follow lost, `activateNavigationTracking()` restores `TRACKING_GPS`
